    Simple Satellite Operations  sso_version.h

    AUTO-GENERATED by CMake from cmake/sso_version.h.in -- do not edit.
    The values are baked in at configure time from `git`; CMake is told to
    reconfigure when HEAD moves (see CMakeLists.txt), so a plain rebuild
    after a commit picks up the new hash.

    Every tool calls sso_version_handle() as the first line of main() so
    `<tool> -V` / `<tool> --version` prints the built commit -- handy for
    stamping a pass sheet with exactly which build flew the pass.

